
This software only runs on modern versions of linux, starting with
linux 6.13.  It makes extensive use of non-portable
file-descriptor-based mount calls and file system namespace
facilities.

To get the software, run:

    git clone github.com:stanford-scs/jai.git
    cd jai

To build from git, you will need autoconf and automake:

    ./autogen.sh
    ./configure
    make

If building from a release tarball, autotools are not required:

    ./configure
    make

To install (must be root for setuid):

    sudo make install

To override the installation prefix:

    ./configure --prefix=/usr
    make
    sudo make install

Most of the tests require a setuid root version of jai to test.  Since
people's build directories are often mounted nosuid, make `jai.suid`
in the top of your build directory a symbolic link to a place with a
setuid executable.  You can run:

    sudo test/setup-setuid.sh

to do this automatically in /var/tmp, which is generally mounted
setuid capable.
